What you need to know:

Lampard achieved a fourth-place finish in his first season in charge to secure a place in the Champions League despite a transfer ban and the sale of Eden Hazard to Real Madrid.However, his Premier League points-per-game average of 1.67 is the lowest for any Chelsea manager in the Abramovich era."I am disappointed not to have had the time this season to take the club forward and bring it to the next level," said Lampard.